While following the guidelines placed on us through Governor DeWine's orders, let's see how we can share our creativity with one another. Hilltop High School, Junior High School, and Elementary Student Councils are sponsoring a spirit week, "Hilltop's Stay Out of the Fray-cation," that will give you daily opportunities to show everyone how you can still be productive, have fun, be creative while still following the social distancing policies that will help us protect ourselves and one another.

November 2, 2019 at 11:50 AM 

It's been a busy three days!

Thursday, we toured Not Just Popcorn, Hunter's Honey Farm, and Ozark Fisheries. Then, attended the Tenille Townes and Brett Young concert.

Friday we found out Ian recieved a Gold Rating and placed 4th in Division 3 Social Systems at the National Agriscience Fair and toured Fair Oaks Farms. That evening we attended the Jim Wand Hypnotist session and went Duckpin Bowling. We also celebrated Bryce and Laurynn's birthdays!

Today we woke up EARLY to attend the American Degree Ceremony where THREE of our members: Ethan Dunson, Austin Schaffner, and Sam Shilling received their degrees!

Congratulations everyone on an awesome convention! Thank you so much to Mr. King for chaperoning our trip! You've been a life saver!

shared_text:
Millcreek-West Unity FFA
October 24, 2019 at 11:15 PM 

Last evening, Ian Hoffman gave his Agriscience Fair presentation to the SAVE committee. His was one of 12 projects selected from across the nation to move onto national competition after winning Division 3 Social Science Systems at State FFA Convention in May! We are excited for him as he takes his project to present at the National FFA Convention next week in Indy!

Also, Rimm Kleen has offered their land for the FFA to farm this year. Today our 8th period Animal and Plant Science class worked with Wilbur-Ellis to collect a few soil samples to test the soil. We are excited to start this new experience! Thank you Rimm Kleen and Wilbur-Ellis for giving our students this unique opportunity!
